<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-332-134  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 332 134.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC User  May 10 1989 n106 p79(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT EMAP Business and Computer Publications1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Comdex report: ALR FlexCache 33-386Z. (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Lavin, Paul.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   ALR UK (product introduction).andO;Product:   Advanced Logic Research FlexCache 33-386Z (Microcomputer).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionMicrocomputersSystem Design.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotographtable.andO;Caption:   Preview. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>ALR FlexCache 33/386ZandM;All set for a gala introduction at the PC User Show is a blindingly fastsmall footprint ALR carrying a 33MHz 386 and a 2,500 pounds sterling pricetag.andM;For that paltry sum of money, you don't get a fully configured system, ofcourse.andP;  The low cost leader comes with a single megabyte of RAM, a3-1/2-inch 720Kb/1.44Mb disk drive, 101-keyboard and, importantly, nomonitor, video adaptor, hard disk or controller.andP;  These features areavailable at additional cost.andM;When you buy a small footprint desktop PC you give up expandability.andP;  InIngenious design by ALR blunts the impact of this inescapable consequence byproviding two half-height 5-1/4-inch drive bays, with a 3-1/2-inch floppydrive positioned vertically alongside.andP;  Behind the 3-1/2-inch floppy is roomfor a similar-sized hard disk.andM;There are a growing number of above-100 Mb 3-1/2-inch Winchesters around.andP;  Ifyou choose to plug one of those in you can have both floppy disk formats, atape streamer and the Winchester drive.andP;  That's something I can't even withmy Apricot tower.andM;Slots are at a premium, though.andP;  There are seven in all.andP;  One holds thefloppy/IO adaptor, another will see your video card, and another will beneeded for the hard disk interface.andP;  This leaves you with three plus thememory slot.andM;One slot is an ALR proprietary 32-bit slot for memory.andP;  Instead of providinga board festooned with Industry Standard (Compaq's capitalization) SIMMslots, they have gone the route of ALR-only memory modules.andM;While ALR's memory prices have not been as extortionate as others during thememory drought, I am wary of getting stuck with ALR's memory buying cloutwhen I need more megabytes fast.andP;  Maybe the situation will change this year,but a lot of future purchase decisions will be shaped by last year'snonsense.andM;The motherboard can be expanded to 2Mb before the memory slot is invoked.andO;The 33MHz 386 has an 82385 cache controller with 32Kb of fast static RAM.andM;If ALR can stick to its price and delivery schedule, a lot of othermanufacturers will need to get a move on to have any hopes of shifting theirtardy and over-priced kit.andO;</TEXT></DOC>